HEADWORD: Clotheshorse
<hw>Clothes"horse`</hw> <pr>(kl⟦omac⟧z"h⟦ocir⟧rs`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A frame to hang clothes on.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a person who is conspicuous for dressing
